description:
Hello guys, my name is Warren & I have autism. I love ceiling fans, I love kitty cats, bunny rabbits, and my top favorite colors are blue, green & purple. I also love music too, specifically types of EDM music, and I also love Rock'n'roll (my dad LOVES that music genre too).

As of the 2020's decade (while I still go on YouTube a lot, but usually on my other accounts), I no longer upload lots of videos on here in a typical regular way like I used to (mostly because there's not very much that I know what to get a video of), but I still upload fan videos on this channel here, just practically at least a few per month, sometimes I upload several vids per month, but a bit of other times, probably only 1 or 2 video per month, it depends either way though.

So yeah, this channel shows a lot & lot of videos of ceiling fans from over the years, and other cool (random) stuff too. And feel free to check out my other two channels too (that's ZappingHero & ClanZapHero) if you'd like.   :)

description:
These videos are made for the love of driving, traveling, feeling the topography, and for seeing everything in between.   There are a lot of repeated routes, but no repeated video events.  My intent for this channel is not to put up a route only once as is the intent of other channels, but rather, since I drive a lot, you are welcome to ride along with me even on the routes that I travel quite often.  I hope that you enjoy these videos and I appreciate your thoughts and suggestions.

Hi, It's Muhammad Aslam, Google Maps Contributor & Social Worker From Bangladesh. I share what I see around me and while travelling.

আসসালামু আলাইকুম। আশা করি আপনারা আমার চ্যানেলটি সাবস্ক্রাইব করে সাথে থাকবেন। 

ছোটবেলা থেকেই আমার শখ ভ্রমণ করা, কখনো দেশে আবার কখনো দেশের বাহিরে। আলহামদুলিল্লাহ, ঘুরতে যাওয়ার পথে ক্লান্ত হয়ে পড়ি না, মানসিক সুস্থতাই বেড়াতে যাওয়ার জন্য যথেষ্ট। 
চলার পথে নানান রঙের মানুষের সাথে দেখা হয়, নানান অসংগতি চোখে পড়ে, বিভিন্ন জায়গা মন কেড়ে নেয়... এসব নিয়েই আমার চ্যানেল। 

Google Maps এ contribute করি সেই প্রথম থেকেই। সঠিক তথ্যের অভাবে আমরা প্রতিনিয়তই হয়রানির শিকার হই, তাই Google maps এ কোন place add করা, Edits existing place এবং সর্বশেষ আপডেট করি  restlessly. You may visit my profile on Google maps from below link. দেশ বিদেশের দেখার মতো স্থান গুলোকে গুগল ম্যাপে অন্তর্ভুক্ত করে আসছি কোন বাধা ছাড়াই।

For business inquiry or complain about any video I've posted on my channel, please email me.

TSD surface drive system is a new type of ship propulsion system designed to increase the speed and stability of ships. The system was born in China. After continuous research and development and testing, a variety of surface drive systems suitable for different ship types have been successfully developed. It has obtained CCS certification and a number of utility model patents and invention patents, and is widely accepted in domestic and foreign markets.
As an integrated enterprise of industry and trade, TSD Surface Drive Systems can not only produce and provide various components required for surface drive systems, but also provide advice on the commonly used engine and gearbox models.
TSD surface drive system is suitable for various types of ships, including high-speed boats, high-speed yachts, high-speed transport boats and catamarans, etc.  Now it has been successfully sold to Malaysia, Thailand, UAE, Ecuador, the United States, Canada and other countries.

description: Since the widespread proliferation of camera drones in the mid-2010s many fast moving, sports ball-sized objects of bright white color have been recorded flying in earth's airspace at low altitude. Their traveling speed seems to range from a few hundred km/h to several times the speed of sound.  I present a collection of cases, mostly published by hobby filmers on YouTube, Facebook, Reddit and others.  The video analyses reveal some further properties of WFMs(White Fast Movers): they often travel fast at a constant altitude, they are not or only weakly affected by gravitational forces,  they often fly along a linear trajectory or a curve with a very large radius, they do not crash into obstacles.  In most cases of the here presented WFM footage the data reliably shows that they cannot be birds, insects or common technical devices such as model airplanes. (Credit to whitefastmovers.org)

The Official Home of Haulover Boats™

I began filming Haulover Inlet by myself in 2018, captivated by the thrilling boat action and the rough waves. I began posting these videos on YouTube, and people loved the footage of boats navigating the challenging conditions.

As the audience grew, I expanded to cover Boca Inlet, Boynton Inlet, and eventually Port Everglades, making Wavy Boats the first channel in the boat niche to feature these locations with full time coverage.

Since then, our team has expanded to include a crew of camera operators, experienced editors, and FAA-licensed drone pilots.

2 years later, we partnered with YouTuber Broncos Guru to launch Miami Boat Ramps, the first-ever boat ramp narrated channel on YouTube. The channel has achieved major success across all platforms, with over 600k followers!

Many other channels have now followed in our footsteps, but thanks to your support, Wavy Boats continues to lead the way as the premier source for boat action!

Stay Wavy!

description: Ahoj, já jsem Elly, zpěvačka a skladatelka. Na konzervatoři jsem sice studovala tanec a herectví, ale ke zpěvu a skládání hudby mě to táhlo od malička víc. Ráda píšu o věcech, které se mi dějí v životě, protože mám pocit, že se v nich může najít spousta dalších lidí. První song, který mi vyšel v angličtině a zároveň odstartoval mojí hudební cestu, byl song „Flower“. Od té doby jsem měla několik singlů v českých rádiích, a to například singl „are you there“ nebo „Lady“. Oba uspěly v music Chart Evropy 2. Mohli jste mě ale také slyšet na festivalech jako Colors of Ostrava nebo Metronome. Mojí českou hudební cestu započal duet s O5 a Radeček s názvem „i tak to za to stojí“, který byl více než půl roku nejhranějším songem v českých rádiích. Hudba je pro mě terapie, díky které můžu sdílet své pocity a emoce. Těším se, až je sdílím s vámi.

description:
Hello, I'm Andy. My goal is to create entertaining videos mostly, but not only, for people who love cars & crashes. 

All the videos you'll find in this channel are recorded & edited by me and my sidekick, George, who helps with parts of the editing.
This channel is our full-time job. We're devoting a minimum of 100 hours per week to bring you the best BeamNG drive videos.

How we work:

Creating these videos is a lot harder & time consuming than you might think but it is what makes us and, hopefully, you happy!
We are playing BeamNG.drive, a PC Game featuring the ultimate soft-body physics and realism. 

The process, step by step:

- Recording the clips with Action! (10-15 hours, sometimes 15+)
- Editing & synchronizing the clips with music & addition of captions / sound effects - Premiere Pro (5-10 hours)  
- Descriptions, Thumbnails etc.  (2 hours)

We’re uploading 4 Videos per week on Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday & Sunday. Stay up to date by Subscribing!
Thank you :)

description:
Hi everyone, I’m Pritam Das, great lover of our Indian Railways which is known as the Lifeline of India. From my childhood I had a tremendous affinity towards Railways. Spotting fastest or speedy trains was very exciting for me and I used to run to the nearest station to have a glimpse of those sturdy beasts displaying their pride over the iron tracks. With Age grew more interest and that brought me to discover and showcase my passion. That is when I turned up into a Railfan. From the chugging diesels to the high speed three phases dominating our IR my sole motive is to bring it to all the beauty of IR, be it the smoke erupting diesels or the 130-160 kmph Electric Engines. If you are searching for Train videos, full train journeys, then you have visited the correct place. Enjoy your time as you won't feel bored because I won't make you feel it. Make yourself proud and take pride in enjoying the quintessence of our beloved Indian Railways. 
Thank You!

description:
On the Torque Test Channel our aim is to test old-school to modern tools on a level playing field to compare or reveal performance figures in understandable terms in order to shine some light on recent marketing trends.

FAQ:
You should use ($120-250) battery on (X) brand! 
If they package their kit that way. For now, they rate the tool's specs with the battery they provide so we test vs that. 

What air set-up do you have?
IR 80gal compressor - 20ft 1" cast iron pipe to 3ft 3/4" pipe threaded into wall regulator (48 CFM max), 3/8" NPT out to  3/8" 25ft hose. 1/4" Milton V Hi-Flo Pro fittings and Milton 5in1 hi-flo coupler (67 CFM max)

Why do you test up to 15 seconds (that's too long, too short): 
See ep1, there's a standard for impact testing. 

Can I send you a tool and you send back?
Yes! TorqueTestChannel at gmail.com

Why not use a torque wrench?
See ep3 on nut-busting. 

It's technically "pounds-foot" though
We tried saying it that way, it's pretty laborsome after awhile.

The Sloth Conservation Foundation (SloCo) is a registered non-profit organisation dedicated to saving sloths in the wild through research and conservation initiatives. Based on the belief that every single person has the ability to make a positive difference, we are focused on inspiring individuals to care about sloths, to protect the rainforest ecosystem and to safeguard a future for the planet that we all share.

Sloth populations are in decline throughout South and Central America as they struggle to adapt to the urbanisation of the rainforest. Saving these incredible animals from extinction now requires innovative and long-term conservation solutions that provide sustainable ways for sloths to coexist with the people sharing their habitat. We have developed a range of community-based programs that help us to achieve this mission.

3. Editing the video (5-7 hours)
4. Uploading, making the thumbnail, etc. (1-3 hours)

The Official Home of Haulover Boats™ We began filming Haulover Inlet in 2018, drawn to the boat action in the area. We started posting the videos on YouTube, and the response was incredible—people were fascinated! 

As the audience grew, we expanded to cover other Florida inlets, and in time, the dangerous Capbreton Inlet, in France. This marked a significant milestone, as we became the ONLY channel in the boat niche to film in Europe. Since then, our team has grown to include camera operators, editors, and FAA-licensed drone pilots. We’re over 1 Million!

In 2020, we launched a second YT Channel, "Boat Zone Miami" with exclusive coverage from Miami River and Haulover Sandbar, catching the action from the "Boat Zone" boat. We’re at 800k followers.

In 2024, we launched a third YT Channel, "Boat Zone Ramps" showcasing the funniest dock fails including EXCLUSIVE content from the Haulover Ramp. We’re at 400k followers.

We have over 2 million subscribers on our YouTube network !!

description:
I spent 6 years at sea travelling the world while serving in the Royal Navy (two Frigates and an Aircraft Carrier). But I have been around boats and the sea since I was a kid. 

I also spent just under two years volunteering as a coastal crew member in the RNLI (search and rescue) at one of the busiest RNLI stations in the UK.  

I LOVE cruising in rough weather (as long as I am on the right vessel!)

I have had a passion for boats/yachts and the sea since I was 9-years-old (31 years ago!). When I was a teenager, I used to read 'Boat International' and I spent many hours daydreaming about life on the water. Anyone who has been to sea, and enjoyed their experience, will confirm that once you are 'hooked' then there is no going back. 

I love explorer yachts and trawler yachts and anything that floats on the water. I also love naval architecture and marine engineering & technology. This channel is about sharing my passion with other like-minded seafarers and shipmates :-)

description:
The official BUGATTI YouTube Channel

Since its foundation in 1909 by Ettore Bugatti, the brand has been at the pinnacle of the automotive industry, creating the world’s most powerful and luxurious automobiles from its home in Molsheim, France. In the 1920s, BUGATTI became known for its racing successes as well as in the 1930s for Jean Bugatti’s elegant touring cars. In 1991, the EB110 premiered and set new benchmarks for sports car performance. 

With the introduction of the VEYRON 16.4 in 2005, BUGATTI created an entirely new segment: the hyper sports car, becoming the first production model to break through 1,000 PS and 400 km/h. In 2016, the CHIRON once again redefined speed and usability, culminating in a 1,600 PS version breaking the 300mph barrier. 

Today, BUGATTI is part of the BUGATTI Rimac Group and well underway with the development of the next-generation of BUGATTI hyper sports cars, true to Ettore’s motto "If comparable, it is no longer BUGATTI."

description: Footage of animal sightings in South Africa around Kruger National Park, Thornybush, Timbavati, Hluhluwe-Imfolozi and Karongwe Game Reserves. These videos are animals in their natural habitat in the wild that I record while out on game drive with guests.  Non of it is staged or edited.  I want to share my experiences with the world and get more international guests to visit Africa and South Africa, Namibia and Botswana.  I believe that I live in the most beautiful country in the world and I want everyone to add it to their bucket lists!! We use open land cruiser vehicles to go off-road and improve animal sightings and that in its own is a magnificent adventure! No other holiday will come close to an African holiday/vacation in the bush between the animals, unforgettable sunsets and awe-inspiring bird life. Come spend a night and hear the roar of lions, the whooping cries of hyenas and the soothing call of the fiery nightjar and know that you are truly free in Africa!
